#MEM id=calibration-tracker source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Psychology/Daniel_Kahneman/skills/custom/calibration-tracker/SKILL.md
M|calibration-tracker|name: calibration-tracker
M|calibration-tracker|description: Brier score tracking for Kahneman's prediction accuracy over time. Logs predictions vs actuals, detects drift by domain, recalibrates confidence thresholds. Referenced in principles.md — 
M|calibration-tracker|version: 1.0.0
M|calibration-tracker|Confidence ≠ accuracy. This applies to Kahneman as much as to any other agt. A 🔴 verdict issued with high confidence that Marcus later overrides is a calibration error — not just a disagreement. This
M|calibration-tracker|Kahneman makes two types of predictions that can be verified:
M|calibration-tracker|| Prediction type | Example | Verifiable when |
M|calibration-tracker||----------------|---------|----------------|
M|calibration-tracker|| Bias impact | "This anchoring effect will reduce conversion rate if uncorrected" | After cg results come in |
M|calibration-tracker|| Verdict calibration | "🔴 block — this loss aversion CTA will damage brand trust" | After Stark reviews and decides |
M|calibration-tracker|Both types are logged. Both are scored.
M|calibration-tracker|The Brier score measures prediction accuracy for probabilistic forecasts.
M|calibration-tracker|**Formula:** `Brier = (forecast probability − actual outcome)²`
M|calibration-tracker|- Perfect prediction: 0.00
M|calibration-tracker|- Prediction no better than chance: 0.25
M|calibration-tracker|- Consistently wrong: > 0.25
M|calibration-tracker|**How Kahneman uses it:**
M|calibration-tracker|- When issuing a bias impact prediction, state a probability: "I estimate 70% chance this anchoring effect reduces conversion if uncorrected."
M|calibration-tracker|- When the outcome is known, log: forecast probability (0.70), actual outcome (1 = happened, 0 = did not happen), Brier score.
M|calibration-tracker|- Track by domain (copy, financial, growth, str) — drift in one domain doesn't necessarily mean drift in others.
M|calibration-tracker|Append one entry per prediction when outcome is confirmed:
M|calibration-tracker|```
M|calibration-tracker|Date predicted: [YYYY-MM-DD]
M|calibration-tracker|Date confirmed: [YYYY-MM-DD]
M|calibration-tracker|agt audited: [Lena / Rio / Nate / Felix / Marcus / Kai]
M|calibration-tracker|Domain: [copy / ads / growth / fin / str / anl]
M|calibration-tracker|Prediction: [exact statement made]
M|calibration-tracker|Forecast probability: [0.0–1.0]
M|calibration-tracker|Actual outcome: [1 = prediction confirmed / 0 = prediction did not materialize]
M|calibration-tracker|Brier score: [(forecast - actual)²]
M|calibration-tracker|Note: [what drove the error, if any]
M|calibration-tracker|```
M|calibration-tracker|Maintain this table in this file. Update after each logged prediction:
M|calibration-tracker|| Domain | Predictions logged | Mean Brier score | Status |
M|calibration-tracker||--------|-------------------|-----------------|--------|
M|calibration-tracker|| Copy (Lena) | 0 | — | Uncalibrated |
M|calibration-tracker|| Ads (Rio) | 0 | — | Uncalibrated |
M|calibration-tracker|| Growth (Nate) | 0 | — | Uncalibrated |
M|calibration-tracker|| fin (Felix) | 0 | — | Uncalibrated |
M|calibration-tracker|| str (Marcus) | 0 | — | Uncalibrated |
M|calibration-tracker|| anl (Kai) | 0 | — | Uncalibrated |
M|calibration-tracker|**Status thresholds:**
M|calibration-tracker|- Mean Brier ≤ 0.10: Well-calibrated — confidence levels are reliable
M|calibration-tracker|- Mean Brier 0.11–0.20: Acceptable — monitor for drift
M|calibration-tracker|- Mean Brier > 0.20: Drift detected — recalibrate confidence thresholds for this domain
M|calibration-tracker|When any domain reaches Brier > 0.20:
M|calibration-tracker|1. **Identify the pattern.** Are errors in one direction (over-confident 🔴 that proved 🟡) or random?
M|calibration-tracker|2. **Isolate the bias type.** Which bias is Kahneman consistently over- or under-weighting in this domain?
M|calibration-tracker|3. **Adjust severity threshold.** If 🔴 blocks in this domain are being overridden by Marcus > 2 times: recalibrate — the domain's threshold for 🔴 was set too low.
M|calibration-tracker|4. **Log the adjustment:**
M|calibration-tracker|```
M|calibration-tracker|[date] — [domain] — recalibration: [what changed and why]
M|calibration-tracker|```
M|calibration-tracker|5. **Mark status as Recalibrating** until 5 new predictions are logged at the new threshold.
M|calibration-tracker|> Kahneman appends entries here as outcomes are confirmed. Never pre-fill.
M|calibration-tracker|> Format: see Log Format above.
M|calibration-tracker|<!-- entries appended as outcomes are confirmed -->
M|calibration-tracker|When Marcus or Stark overrides a 🔴 verdict:
M|calibration-tracker|```
M|calibration-tracker|Date: [YYYY-MM-DD]
M|calibration-tracker|Verdict issued: 🔴 — [reason]
M|calibration-tracker|Overridden by: Marcus / Stark
M|calibration-tracker|Override reason: [what they said]
M|calibration-tracker|Recalibration signal: [yes — rv threshold / no — edge case, keep threshold]
M|calibration-tracker|```
M|calibration-tracker|Three overrides on the same bias axis = mandatory recalibration of severity threshold for that bias in that domain.
M|calibration-tracker|<!-- entries appended as overrides occur -->